# mount-drive config. One drive per line: UUID|MOUNTPOINT|DISPLAY_NAME
# Lines starting with # and blank lines are ignored.
# UUIDs come from `lsblk -o NAME,UUID`.
# MOUNTPOINT must exist on disk and be owned by you (the script will not create it).
#
# Examples:
# 4C6E97526E973424|/home/aditya/Media/Sanctuary|Sanctuary
# 1C03-2149|/home/aditya/Media/echoSD|echoSD
# 9EC4-6986|/home/aditya/Media/Music-backup|Music-backup
